```css
/* src/app/globals.css */

/* Import necessary dependencies */
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

/* Define dark mode styles using the 'dark' class provided by Tailwind CSS */
.dark {
  /* Set the background color to a dark color */
  background-color: #1a1d23;

  /* Set the text color to a light color */
  color: #fff;

  /* Update the link color to a lighter color */
  a {
    color: #66d9ef;
  }

  /* Update the link hover color to a darker color */
  a:hover {
    color: #44a0e6;
  }
}

/* Define styles for the rest of the application */
body {
  /* Set the font family to a sans-serif font */
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;

  /* Set the font size to 16px */
  font-size: 16px;

  /* Set the line height to 1.5 */
  line-height: 1.5;
}

/* Define styles for headings */
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  /* Set the font weight to bold */
  font-weight: bold;

  /* Set the color to a dark color */
  color: #333;
}

/* Define styles for paragraphs */
p {
  /* Set the font size to 16px */
  font-size: 16px;

  /* Set the line height to 1.5 */
  line-height: 1.5;
}
```

Note: This code assumes that you have already installed Tailwind CSS in your project and have configured it to use the `dark` class for dark mode styles. If you haven't installed Tailwind CSS, you can do so by running the command `npm install tailwindcss` or `yarn add tailwindcss` in your terminal. You will also need to configure Tailwind CSS to use the `dark` class by adding the following code to your `tailwind.config.js` file:
```javascript
module.exports = {
  // ...
  darkMode: 'class',
  // ...
}
```